    "body": "We’ve started the exploration understanding which are the **use cases** consumers of data coming from `src/app_service/service/token/service.nim` and also which is the data coming from it (being this data all **pure list of tokens** from **supported app sources** (nowadays _uniswap, status_ and _custom_ lists)).\r\n\r\n**App use cases:**\r\n-\r\nDefinition of app use cases in a high level way:\r\n- To add new `permission` in a community via `Holding dropdown`.\r\n- To validate and avoid repetition of `name` and `symbol` whenever a new community token is minted.\r\n- To display all tokens from a specific source in `Wallet / Settings / Manage tokens / Tokens List Tab`.\r\n\r\n**Goal:**\r\n-\r\nAll of these use cases will need the same data source but UI representation will be different, so the aim of this analysis is:\r\n- Identify if service can present data in a better/easy/basic and generic way and try to avoid data filtering at this point if it’s just a visual representation issue. \r\n- Identify which are the models needed and try to minimise them designing them in a way that they can be reused across different views avoiding repetition of code and uncertainty when deciding which is the real source of information for each use case. Models should relay only in 1 source of truth, that means, data provided by the service.\r\n- Analyse current stores definition, only the ones affected by the specific service use cases, and expose the new models in a single place.\r\n\r\n**Subtasks:**\r\n-\r\n Here the subtasks needed to go through and work on all explained points:\r\n- [x] Definition of new service, wallet submodule, controller, view and models (flat tokens list and by symbol tokens list). Also add these new models in the correct qml `store`:  [Ongoing draft PR ](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/12489)\n- [x] https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/12501\n- [x] https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/12502\r\n- [ ] https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/12513\r\n- [x] https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/12511\r\n- [x] https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/12512\r\n- [ ] https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/12668\r\n- [ ] Clean up token_service once all other components like community use the model.\r\n- [ ] rename token service to asset service\r\n\r\n**NOTE:** After this example is fully covered, next step will be exploring `src/app_service/service/wallet_account/service.nim` and try to follow same approach.",
